# Keep the build context minimal and never stream the secret (.env with
# GRAFANA_ADMIN_PASSWORD) to the Docker daemon (WX-274).  Ignore everything,
# then allow only the two config files the Dockerfiles actually COPY.  This
# guarantees .env can never be baked into an image layer even if a COPY is
# later broadened by mistake.  The Dockerfiles themselves are read as build
# instructions regardless of this file, so they need no allow-entry.
*
!prometheus.yml
!otel-collector-config.yml
